1. Master Prompt (Best Starting Point)
First Prompt :
Create a modern, responsive portfolio web application using React (Vite) and Tailwind CSS.

Design style:
- Clean, minimal, professional UI
- Soft color palette (white, gray, with subtle accent like purple or blue)
- Smooth animations and transitions
- Glassmorphism and card-based layout
- Fully responsive (mobile-first)

Sections to include:
1. Hero Section
   - Name: Nisha Yadav
   - Title: Full Stack Developer
   - Short tagline about building scalable web apps
   - CTA buttons: "View Projects", "Contact Me"

2. About Me
   - 5+ years experience summary
   - Focus on React, Node.js, MongoDB
   - Passion for building scalable and performant apps

3. Skills Section
   - Frontend: React, Vue, Angular, JavaScript
   - Backend: Node.js, Express, MongoDB
   - Tools: Jenkins, Azure DevOps, Git
   - Show skills with icons and progress bars

4. Experience Timeline
   - Genpact (2022–Present)
   - R Systems International (2020–2022)
   - Timeline UI with cards

5. Projects Section
   - Open Retro (highlight project)
   - Just Vegan
   - MERN Auth
   - Show project cards with:
     - Title
     - Description
     - Tech stack
     - GitHub + Live links

6. Contact Section
   - Email, phone, LinkedIn
   - Contact form UI

7. Footer
   - Minimal with social links

Extra features:
- Dark/Light mode toggle
- Smooth scroll navigation
- Hover animations
- Sticky navbar

Tech requirements:
- React + Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- Component-based structure

2. Advanced UI Prompt (For Premium Design ✨)
Second Prompt :
Design a premium developer portfolio UI for a senior full stack developer.

UI style:
- Modern SaaS-inspired layout
- Glassmorphism + subtle gradients
- Animated background (blur blobs or grid)
- Micro-interactions on hover
- Smooth page transitions (Framer Motion)

Key design elements:
- Floating navbar with blur effect
- Hero section with gradient text and animated typing effect
- Card-based sections with shadow and hover lift
- Timeline with vertical progress indicator
- Project cards with image preview and hover overlay
- Skill badges with icons and glow effect

Typography:
- Bold headings, clean sans-serif font
- Proper spacing and hierarchy

Color palette:
- Dark mode default
- Primary: Indigo / Purple gradient
- Accent: Cyan / Pink highlights

Make it look like a top-tier developer portfolio (inspired by modern SaaS landing pages).

3. Component-Level Prompts (Very Useful)
Third Prompt:

👉 Hero Section
Create a modern hero section for a portfolio with:
- Name: Nisha Yadav
- Title: Full Stack Developer
- Animated typing effect
- CTA buttons
- Gradient text
- Background blur animation

👉 Project Cards
Create reusable project card components using React and Tailwind with:
- Image preview
- Title and description
- Tech stack badges
- GitHub and Live buttons
- Hover animation with scale and shadow

👉 Experience Timeline
Create a vertical timeline UI using React and Tailwind:
- Company name, role, duration
- Expandable details
- Animated scroll reveal